                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="66243" author="linda" created="Tue, 10 Sep 2013 19:23:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The following bullet was included in Section 1.1 with &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6133/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6133/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;NFS and CIFS export:  Lustre files can be re-exported using NFS (via Linux knfsd) or CIFS (via Samba) enabling them to be shared with non-Linux clients, such as Microsoft* Windows* and Apple* Mac OS X*.&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
No other mention of Samba is made in the manual.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assigning to HPPD triage. This needs to be assigned to a subject expert to create the new section on setting up and tuning Samba on Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56852" author="adilger" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2013 18:37:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Very minimal change &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/6133&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/6133&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We really need a full section to describe how to set up and tune Samba on Lustre, so this bug should be kept open.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56847" author="adilger" created="Tue, 23 Apr 2013 18:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is still worthwhile to add &quot;Windows&quot; into any section that mentions Samba or CIFS or SMB.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="54279" author="jlevi" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 17:20:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linda to verify with Bryon and Peter if this should be in the project.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
